originalText.text: Took the seastreak from Pier 11 Manhattan to Sandy Hook New Jersey and back. Round trip for $49 or something. The boat was clean and spacious, good seating options in shade with AC, part sun, or full sun on top deck. I opted for that upper deck both trips, wind in my hair enjoying the views. Seating inside the boat has ice cold AC pumping and comfortable and well spaced seats. Seating gets tighter spaced as you go towards the top. The very top has both seating and standing area. There's a bar on board where you can get alcoholic or non-alcoholic beverages. There are several bathrooms. You can bring your own snacks or drinks on board. The trip was super efficient, 35 minutes each way. They provide shuttle services at the destination, which are on time and efficient. At first I thought the price tag was high for the round trip ticket, but later when I saw the boat and the process and enjoyed the experience, I realized it was completely worth the price tag. I would definitely do this trip again in a heartbeat. I would also consider doing the whale watch or other routes with this company. Overall it was more of an extremely pleasant memorable experience rather than just a commute, well worth the money.

originalText.text:
I'd like to complain about 2 things that Seastreak should really work on...
1. If you're staying for a few days you can't park in the lot next to the terminal. But really, why make folks with bags walk a couple of blocks (10 min)? There's no drop off place for suitcases.

2. The parking lot is terrible! Almost broke a wheel trying to get my suitcase to the ferry over the stones.  It was not marked where i should walk so thats another complaint.

Then when I got back, I was so happy I wasn't parked in the 1st lot, it had water up to some bumpers of cars since it had just rained. And getting to that 2nd lot (overnight parking) would have required me carrying my suitcase over my head walking down the middle of the street with rain water up to my calves IF not for the nice man I asked for a ride.

Some party needs to do something, either Seastreak or The Highlands Dept of whatever. It was not a pleasant experience for a first-time user of the ferry to NYC.

On another note, the ferry itself was clean, the crew helpful and the schedule on time. Easy way to travel to Manhattan.
